he summer shore resorts, just north of the border with Maryland, at the other end of the ferry from Cape May, New Jersey.  Peaches and other fruit were a big cash crop early in this century, but a blight killed most of the orchards, some of which are stil
\hich\af1\dbch\af13\loch\f1 l\hich\af1\dbch\af13\loch\f1 
 standing, eerily beautiful, like rows of surreal black skeletons.  Today much of the country's scrapple is made in Delaware, but the main agribusiness is the "chicken factories" where poultry is processed and packaged for supermarkets -\~
- some people wil\hich\af1\dbch\af13\loch\f1 l\hich\af1\dbch\af13\loch\f1  tell you lower Delaware is God's country, but many will tell you it's Frank Purdue's.
\par {\pntext\pard\plain\ltrpar \rtlch\fcs1 \ab\af1\afs20 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f1\fs20\cf6\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid0\langfenp1033\insrsid4005967 \hich\af1\dbch\af13\loch\f1 1:\hich\f1 \'b6\loch\f1 10\tab}}\pard \ltrpar\ql \li0\ri14\sl480\slmult1\widctlpar
