ade the "Racketeer Influenced and Corrupt Organizations" chapter part of the federal criminal code, effective 15 October 1970, to be able to prosecute organized crime for using legitimate businesses as fronts or money laundries for the proceeds of crimina
\hich\af1\dbch\af13\loch\f1 l\hich\af1\dbch\af13\loch\f1 
 activity.  It defines "pattern of racketeering activity" to be at least two felony violations of certain state or federal statutes committed by the same person within 10 years, and at least one act has to have been after this law went into effect.  The s
\hich\af1\dbch\af13\loch\f1 t\hich\af1\dbch\af13\loch\f1 atute makes it a crime to use money from such racketeering activity to start, buy, or run a business engaged in interstate commerce or to conspire with somebody else to do so.
\par {\pntext\pard\plain\ltrpar \rtlch\fcs1 \ab\af1\afs20 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f1\fs20\cf6\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid0\langfenp1033\insrsid4005967 \hich\af1\dbch\af13\loch\f1 5:\hich\f1 \'b6\loch\f1 15\tab}}\pard \ltrpar\ql \li0\ri0\sl480\slmult1\widctlpar
